    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-13T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.116/156: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers in China and
                            Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="98" xml:id="d87fn98">At Peiping, Chungking, Tokyo, and Shanghai.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-13T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 13, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Peiping’s 606, October 6, 6 p.m., Tokyo’s 640 [<hi rend="italic">646</hi>],
                    October 6, 9 a.m., and Tientsin’s 191, October 7, 5 p.m., and 192, October 8,
                        noon,<note n="99" xml:id="d87fn99">Last three telegrams not printed.</note>
                    in regard to importation of radio equipment. The Department requests that Tokyo
                    notify the Japanese Foreign Office that the proposed arrangements are not
                    satisfactory and that the American Government reserves all rights in respect of
                    losses suffered by American interests in consequence of enforcement by the
                    provisional régime of any restrictions on the importation of American radio
                        equipment.<note n="1" xml:id="d87fn1">The Ambassador in Japan addressed a
                        note to the Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs on October 18.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Peiping repeat to Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
